Two methyl groups attached to the benzene rings would also add some melting point elevation, though their effect is comparatively smaller; we can estimate +5°C for each. Lastly, the single ethyl side chain may have a mild effect; let's estimate an increase of about +5°C for its steric hindrance and mass.
Prediction: 5.5 (base for benzene) + 40 (two additional benzene rings) + 160 (two amide groups) + 20 (ketone group) + 10 (two methyl groups) + 5 (ethyl group) = 240.5°C
